author: @davyponte
comment:
THE GLITCH IN TEASERS IS A CODES, THERE ARE A COUTDOWN AND ENDS ON FEBRUARY 17TH:
My theory is very simple:
â€“ Letâ€™s take the first teaser as an example:
it was released on December 23, so 12:23 (expressed as month:day), added to its own code 1:24 (expressed as month:day), results in 2:17, which is February 17th.
â€“ Letâ€™s take the third teaser as another example:
it was released on January 6, so 1:06 (expressed as month:day), added to its own code 1:11 (expressed as month:day), again results in 2:17, which is February 17th.
â€“ Letâ€™s take the fourth reel dedicated to thanking viewers for the views of the four teasers:
it was released on January 16, so 1:16 (expressed as month:day), added to its own code 1:01 (expressed as month:day), results once again in 2:17, which is February 17th.
The result is constant and always comes out as 2:17 â€” essentially February 17th! You can try this with all the teasers that were released; it will always remain 2:17.
Iâ€™m convinced that the Doomsday trailer will be released on February 17th, and that the Endgame â€œtime playâ€ theory doesnâ€™t make sense at all!

the "e" and "ber" is a glitch (to make the code visible not visible as an ambiguity" these characters appear only in the reels of the instagram accounts US, marvel, RDJ and russo brothers. while the character glitch in the instagram account marvel the "e" does not appear but "bre" appears which would be "dicemBRE" in Italian while in English it would be "dicemBRE". the character glitches vary for the reels of the accounts marvel fr (france), marvel de (germany), marvel brazil... you can check! while the 02 is the time... January is made up of 31 days, so the date of publication of the post + post code = 2:16 .. ok, but remember that the reel was published at 10:00pm so 10:00pm + 02 = 12:00pm so 2; 16: 12:00pm and therefore 2: 17: 00:00am!

author: @BUSSYCRACKMON5TER
comment:
I'm piecing this together. I could be WAY off. 
FANTASTIC FOUR POST CREDITS WITH DOOM: After the post credits in Fantastic Four with Doom and Franklin they'll pick up and we'll see the Fantastic Four lose to Doom. Franklin is taken. Reed and the team build a ship to travel the multiverse to follow him. Doom told them Franklin was the key to saving the multiverse. They travel to the recruit. 
STEVE ROGERS TEASER: The scene with Steve could be Doom trying to recruit, much like he might have tried with the Fantastic Four, but he takes the child instead. Leverage? Powers? Who knows. Reed will recruit Steve.
X-MEN TEASER: I think the X-Men and Fantastic Four and Captain America initially fight. Reed warns them of Doom and the incursions and Magneto will die preventing an incursion. This could be the cause of all the destruction. In the comics Polaris and Sugar Man use their powers to boost Magneto to push the incoming earth on a collision course with the 616 back. This is what Magneto was referring to with accepting death in the trailer and the black king accepting the checkmate on the chess board. The X-Men are only in the film briefly. We'll get a spectacular scene of the Fantastic Four and Captain America fighting the X-Men. Captain America vs. Wolverine. Nightcrawler vs. Reed. Gambit, Beast, Monica Rambeau and others will be there. The X-Men are mostly only in this part of the film. Charles and maybe Beast will play larger roles. Monica,  Beast, and Charles leave with the FF and Cap.
THOR'S PRAYER: Thor's prayer is likely after Doom tried to recruit him. Instead, he took Love. Another powerful child. I don't see connections from the comics or other teasers and films in this scene. 
WAKANDA/FF TEASER: The location in the final teaser is the Talokan Necropolis. Thus, desert. This could be before or after the X-Men. In the comics there was a time where Namor and Black Panther went to war. Even while at war, when meeting with the Illuminati they had an uneasy truce. The illuminati met where T'challa was exiled. The Necropolis. In the Black Panther films they showed the Wakandan City of the Dead, the Necropolis. In the comics it was described as where "Wakandans go to die." But perhaps this is Namor's people's. The desert.  Where Talokans are sent to die. By the time we catch up with them Namor and Shuri have been allies for a while and have traded technology. This is the meeting site of the Illuminati. Charles, Hank, Reed, Namor, Shuri, Steve. Shuri is likely giving the Wakanda Forever arm sign to Steve. They've met. They likely won't call themselves the Illuminati, but by meeting at this location that's the reference. It COULD still be Wakanda, but the Black Panther and Wakanda Forever Necropolis and this location don't appear to be the same.  
The (Wakandan) Necropolis is also where Thanos, Namor, and the Cabal meet after Namor betrays the illuminati and helps the Cabal destroy an incursion bound earth, saving the 616 universe and giving them more time. At some point Namor could go to Doom and help him destroy another earth preventing an incursion. Maybe even with Loki, Sentry, and others, forming the Cabal. 
THUNDERBOLTS/NEW AVENGERS POST CREDITS SCENE: I feel like this happens last. With the number of established characters in the plot thus far introducing all the New Avengers and what I'll call the Mighty Avengers would make everything up to now VERY convoluted. I will say Doom might be with the others the whole time posing as Tony. When the Illuminati, (for lack of a better name) arrive the New Avengers go to meet them, they are intercepted by Sam's Mighty Avengers and a fight breaks out. They stop at the sight of Steve (and possibly Tony, Doom in disguise), and reunions happen. I feel like here is where Thor comes into the story again. He arrives via the bifrost. Everyone together again. 
SPECULATION ON THE CLIMAX/RESOLUTION: Tony reveals himself to be Doom. He has the mask, and after this point we'll likely never see his face. I think they'll use Doom/Tony for most of the film for the RDJ face time,  but the climax of the film will reveal that he's Victor Von Doom. RDJ is GREAT at voices and accents and will likely be very clearly distinct from Tony. There won't be a connection between the two. He high jacks Sentry's Void powers and escapes with him to the Void.this is where the children, Doom, the Void (with a direct connection to the Void itself from Loki and Deadpool and Wolverine) start building Battleworld out of destroyed universes. With him will likely be Namor and Loki, the Cabal. Loki's connection to the sacred timeline will likely come into play for the building of battleworld. The scene shifts back to the heroes. The final incursion begins. The ship was designed to withstand the multiversal collapse, they just need to escape the impact. The ship escaping the collision of two Earth's would be a very visually stunning display if cataclysmic destruction,  and the ship struggling to get far enough would play out like the end of Indepence Day. Everything goes white. 

The film logo appears, and the somber version is the Avengers theme from Infinity War's credits plays. 
POST CREDITS SCENE: Doctor Strange or Bruce or someone we didn't see in the film wakes up in bed. They don't recognize where they are. They open the curtains to reveal they're in the void/battleworld. 
NOTES: In the very end we might see Doom on his throne with white robes referencing Secret Wars. Strange as his right hand man wouldn't be out of the question. 
I don't think this is EXACTLY how it will go,  but this is my closest interpretation based on everything we've gotten up until now.

I never fault a movie studio for leaning on nostalgia to fire up fans for a new project, but with Doomsday the nostalgia is the ONLY THING it has going for it. The MCU has been a commercial and creative wasteland since Endgame, and there is no overarching in-universe story driving us toward this movie. I know nostalgia can grab you in the feels without warning, but this cinematic universe has become a dumpster fire. Thereâ€™s nothing RDJ, Evans, or Hemsworth can do about it. 

â€œYou couldnâ€™t live with your own failure. Where did that bring you? Back to me.â€ That line seems prophetic now.

author: @aquasky77
comment:
I know the comedy in Thor: Love and Thunder went too far for many people and that Thor felt too unserious and unkingly. People turned on Taika, even though he gave us Thor: Ragnarok, which actually revived the character. Let's not be ungrateful.

You also have to understand Thorâ€™s state of mind. In Endgame he was dealing with grief, guilt, and trauma after Infinity War. He came close to stopping Thanos and still failed, and that showed in his physical and emotional state. After Endgame, once everything was restored, the guilt lifted but he was left aimless and without purpose.

Loss does not always produce dignity or wisdom. Sometimes it produces apathy, distraction, or shallow humour. That reaction is uncomfortable to watch, which is why people reject it, but discomfort does not make it unrealistic. We are used to seeing people lash out, and sometimes withdraw, but we rarely see characters respond by becoming flippant, goofy, or unserious, even though that is just as human.

The seriousness in this Doomsday teaser exists because Thor is no longer a wanderer. He has purpose again. He has a child to take care of, and the responsibility to raise her the right way. When someone is responsible only for themselves, they can afford to drift not when you have someone else to take care of. That is how I see it anyway.

author: @rocklynfaher3305
comment: It has to be my age combined with the fact that I grew up with these Hero's as my friends and mentors, that they taught me the meaning of honor, courage, integrity, morals, sacrifice, the difference between right and wrong, and  provided me, not just with the answers and lessons my dissolute and selfish parents were too drunk, too abusive, or too stupid to teach, but gave me symbols to emulate.  That must be why these characters and so many of the Marvel movies touch me and so many of my generation so deeply and evoke such powerful emotional responses.  Many times, I wonder; how many children, like me, found solace in and were lifted up by those silly comic book hero's my father sneered at or my mother panned.  Many of the characters came from the same lowly station as myself with ordinary, everyday lives and common-place struggles of their own, but who taught a generation cast adrift that we could rise above our place in the world and if not become hero's ourselves, at least live decent, kind lives and raise our children with love and caring.

author: @ReapTheWhirlwind
comment:
Thor is both serious and silly y'all. Neither incarnation is wrong! Most importantly, both are canon. This particular version of Thor is interesting because he has stakes again. When he has an ideal, a person, or a nation to fight for Thor is unstoppable but when he's alone he tends to be a bit of a joke. Love really centered him in a way being king of Asgard or even an Avenger could never have done and tbh I think Odin would be proud of him. 

One thing that hasn't been shown on-screen yet is the Thorforce and I wonder if it will show up now. Odin's family has a hereditary power that's passed from father to child that grants a lot of raw strength and other abilities. Hela was clearly invested with a decent amount of the Odinforce and that's why it took Ragnarok to kill her. It's one of those comic book powers that does what the story needs it to do and tbh the Avengers will need all the help they can. Especially if Doom is in his Rabum Alal guise.

author: @f0x-0n-f1re
comment:
Imagine if Thor: Love and Thunder had maintained his character development from Infinity and Endgame. It's fantastic that we are getting back a more serious, grounded character; it strongly reminds me of Kratos from the newer God of War games, who desperately wants that stillness rather than war and fighting. 

This scene in the trailer reminds me of several comic panels and even scenes from Thor in the animated Avengers films. 

Also, with this being the Second teaser and grounded in what seems to be fatherhood, I wonder if we will have a more accurate depiction of Doom and the abuse he suffered at the hands of his father, which turned him into the ruthless man he has become.

author: @Afrinaut
comment: I'm sorry, but it's a little late for Thor and Asgard to be treated like real-supernatural gods now. Should have introduced Thor like this in the first Avengers film, and phase 1. Thor being equal to and greater than Hulk in strength, Asgard being magical and feeling lived-in/real, Thor's dynamic with Tony Stark as the themes of god vs man, magic vs science was for the most part ignored, Ironman being paranoid of Asgard's power thus building the Thorbuster suit, & Thor shifting the favor of battle when he teams up with the rest of the Avengers. Thor did not deliver the finishing blow to Thanos; all of his solo movies are mid, we will never see Thor and Odin humble Galactus, we will never see Thor's relationship with the Omega Mutant Storm and the rest ofthe mutants, why did the MCU waste the goddess Sif etc. The only thing great about the Thor movies was the goddess Hela played by the amazing Cate Blanchett. This is what happens when Kevin Feige turned Thor into a comedy-relief character depowered- "ancient alien" with human-super soldier strength, a supernatural species with god tier strangth and battle experience. Thor's character arch is realizing that humanity is brave and that he can count on them, not depowering him because MCU writers don't know how to handle god-like strength in a team-setting and characters. The best writing for Thor in a show, was the animated Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes (and maybe Avengers Assemble).

comment:
"Pibursuca" isÂ a viral internet riddle or meme, a nonsensical word created from taking the middle letters of four common food words (Pizza, Burger, Sushi, Cake) after removing their middle parts, intended to confuse people into thinking it's a deep phrase but it's just silly wordplay that sounds like "pee-bur-soo-kah" or "pie-bazooka," a playful "fake deep" puzzle for social media.Â 

How the Riddle Works:

Start with:Â Pizza, Burger, Sushi, Cake.

Remove the middle part:

Pizza -> Pi

Burger -> Bu

Sushi -> Su

CakeÂ -> Ca

Combine the remaining letters:Â Pi + Bu + Su + Ca =Â Pibursuca.

The "joke":Â When read aloud, it sounds like "Pee-bur-soo-kah," leading people to overthink it, with funny guesses like "pee bazooka" or "suck a peepee".Â 

Why It's Popular:

It's a classic example of a "fake deep" meme designed to make people feel confused or dumb for not getting the simple, silly answer.

It's a social media trend, often shared on platforms like Facebook and Instagram, prompting many comments of bewilderment and attempts to solve it.

author: @mmirekelite56
comment: I love the mcu but I feel that bringing back Steve and Thor is in poor taste.  One of the things that makes a movie good is proper stakes, proper stakes only feel significant and high *if* the end result is irriversible.   Its why the ending of endgame felt so emotional because it was final... but now they bring back Steve, they bring back Thor and they even bring back RDJ... which throws all the stakes of the previous movies out the window and I feel that does a big disservice to the franchise and what it had built up over the years. Whqt is the point of caring if the charqcters make it through if you can just undo everything at any point. That said this is just one thing, the movie isn't out yet so I'm hopeful that it will be a great movie overall nonetheless.

author: @SuperDonny21
comment:
I know this is may sound wishful thinking but I have been thinking about Secret Wars and how it will be done and I don't think it will be like the books as I don't think Marvel will bring back multiple villains to fight the Avengers, F4 etc.

I am however imagining that Marvel may do something similar to Marvel Ultimate Alliance. Near the end, Doom takes Odin's power and becomes a god (temporarily of course due to his Odin sleep) after beating Hulk, X-men etc he revives some of them to be his slaves to fight of the remaining heroes. So I think it would be cool to see something like this happen at the end of Doomsday, have a battle where Doom gains God level powers, defeats all the main heroes but have some of them die in battle including Thor. Then see Doom starting with Thor, resurrect him with green eyes so mind controlled by Doom, then a few more possibly Cpt Marvel and some of the OG X-men. Whilst the remaining heroes who are still alive look on in shock, Doom then mergers 2 universes together (possibly Fox and MCU earth 616) and creates battle world.

This imo could totally work compared to the comic version where all heroes and villains are transported to battleworld to do battle against each other whilst Doom watches with the Beyonders powers in amusement.

author: @Doom10838
comment:
AVENGERS: DOOMSDAY - THE REVISED MASTER SCRIPt its my prediction if marvel heard this it will be awesome
Endgame post credit scene doom tony ke grave ke paas khada hota h aur mask dikhta h aur bas end 
1. The Brutal Start: Thanos is Nothing
Movie ki pehli hi frame mein hum ek bhayanak ladayi ka nateeja dekhte hain. Doctor Doom ek hi punch mein Thanos ka pura skeleton bahar nikal leta hai (Comics ka iconic moment). Bina kisi mehnat ke wo Thanos jaise titan ko mita deta hai. Ye scene pure theater mein sannata phelane ke liye kaafi hai.
2.starting life - happy life of captain in alternate timeline 
3. First Half: The Missing Kids & Steveâ€™s Entry
Wahin se story 616 mein aati hai jahan Red Hulk, Sam Wilson ko maar raha hota hai. Tabhi Mjolnir ke saath Young Steve Rogers ki entry aur "Bhabhi" wala callback from endgame (Peggy ke saath reunion).ye story connect hogi brave new world se jahan red hulk se ladaai ho rha hota h 
4. Interval: The Hopeful Moment
Steve aur Peggy ka Sam se milna aur Avengers Tower mein Fantastic Four ke saath milkar ye realize karna ki Franklin, Love aur Steve ka betaâ€”teeno gayab hain. Aur yeh connect hogi fantastic 4 first step se jahan doom Franklin ko lekar chala jaata h aur fantastic 4 main earth 616 m aate h 
5. Second Half Opening: The TVA Revelation
Interval ke turant baad Steve, Thor aur Reed TVA pahunchte hain. Wahan Loki unhe milta hai (Thor aur Loki ka sabse emotional reunion). Loki unhe h story btata hai:
 * The Kang Massacre: Doom ne kaise Council of Kangs ko kachre ki tarah saaf kiya.
 * Kangâ€™s Final End: Loki batata hai ki Kang ke har ek variant ko Doom ne mita diya hai taaki multiverse mein sirf uska raaj ho.
 * The Defeat of a God: Loki khud accept karta hai ki wo Doom se haar gaya aur ab Incursion shuru ho chuka haiâ€”Universes ek dusre se takra rahe hain.
6. The Void Battle: Tonyâ€™s Consciousness
Loki unhe Void mein bhejta hai jahan Doom ka main "Weapon" (Masked Tony/RDJ) khada hai. Steve aur Tony ki fight hoti hai, lekin jab Steve uske bachche aur Morgan ka naam leta hai, toh Tony ko sab yaad aa jata hai.
 * Hum dekhte hain kaise Doom ne Tony ki grave se uski body nikali aur use apne control mein liya.
7. The Climax: Suit-Up and Assemble
Tony wapas hosh mein aakar Jarvis ke saath suit-up karta hai. The Big Three (Cap, Thor, Iron Man) dobara ek saath khade hote hain.
 * Sam, Steve ko bolta hai "Aap bolo".
 * Steve (with Hammer & Shield): "AVENGERS... ASSEMBLE!"
 * Sab milkar Doom ki sena (Doombots) ko dhote hain.
8. Post-Credit: The Real Mastermind
Saari ladaai ke baad pta chalta hai ki ye sab Doom ka ek chhota sa game tha. Real Doom apna mask nikalta hai aur wo Cillian Murphy nikalta hai. Wo kehta hai: "The Multiverse is now my Battleworld."
Theory ke 3 Sabse Bade Highlights:
 * Thanos & Kang ka disrespect: Ye dikhata hai ki Doom "Ultimate Villain" hai.
 * Thor & Loki Reunion: Fans ko unki aakhri mulakat ka sukoon mil jayega.
 * Two Captains & One Iron Man: Legacy aur Original heroes ka best mix.
Teacher's Remark:
Marvel ki sabse badi problem (Kang) ko bhi story mein itni safai se khatam kiya ki koi sawaal hi nahi bacha. Aur Tony ka grave se nikalna aur wapas Iron Man banna... ye cinema ka sabse bada comeback hoga.
